# ğŸŒ 2ï¸âƒ£ Network Fundamentals

## ğŸ”¹ IP Address

An IP address uniquely identifies a device on a network.

* IPv4 â†’ `192.168.1.10`
* IPv6 â†’ `2001:db8::1`

---

## ğŸ”¹ Subnet Mask

Divides IP into:

* Network portion
* Host portion

Example:

```
IP Address: 192.168.1.10
Subnet Mask: 255.255.255.0
```

---

## ğŸ”¹ Default Gateway

The router IP that connects your local network to the internet.

Example:

```
192.168.1.1
```

---

## ğŸ”¹ Static vs DHCP

| Type   | Description               |
| ------ | ------------------------- |
| Static | Manually assigned IP      |
| DHCP   | Automatically assigned IP |

---

